# C-PHI — Protected Health Information Boundaries

**Non-negotiable.** PHI must not appear in notification payloads, log lines, LLM system prompts, or `audit_log.payload` JSON. PHI may travel **only** in designated channels listed below.

This rule **extends** (does not replace) RSC/PHI rules for `apps/web`: patient-linked data renders server-side; no PHI in client storage or browser-exposed JSON.

## What counts as PHI (for this project)

Treat as PHI any data that identifies a patient or describes their health, including but not limited to:

- Name, email, phone, DOB, address
- Symptoms, diagnoses, medications, supplements, dosages
- Lab values, imaging narratives, intake free text
- Call transcripts, clinical notes, wearable-derived health metrics
- Any combination that could identify an individual in context

When unsure, treat the value as PHI and route it only through allowed channels.

## Allowed PHI channels

| Channel | PHI allowed? | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| LLM **user** message (`analyze-intake`) | **Yes** | Step-1 answers as user content; system prompt stays PHI-free |
| LLM **system** prompt / `services/analysis-engine/prompts/*.md` | **No** | Generic schema instructions only — no example patient narratives |
| `audit_log.payload` | **No** | Entity IDs, action names, gap keys — never field values (C-AUDIT) |
| Application logs (`console`, structured logger) | **No** | Log IDs, actions, status codes; redact or omit content |
| Notification payload types | **No** | Structurally must not accept PHI fields (DoD-7) |
| URL paths / query strings | **No** | Opaque token in path only; never name or health data in URLs |
| Client Components / `localStorage` / sessionStorage | **No** | PHI stays on server; HTML/RSC only |
| Third-party APIs (AssemblyAI, Textract) | **Only if** `baa_verified=true` | Block when BAA not verified (TR-2) |

## API-1 — unauthenticated PHI surface

`GET /api/intake/[token]` is the **only** unauthenticated endpoint returning patient-linked intake state. Token: 128-bit CSPRNG, hash at rest, TTL, rate-limit, lockout (SEC-18).

## Trusted facts for protocol generation

`lib/prompt/format-timeline-for-prompt.ts` excludes unconfirmed `source: ai` fields until clinician-confirmed (DoD-10). Unconfirmed AI data must not affect readiness or generation payloads.

## Failure modes (do not do these)

1. **Embedding example patient narratives in system prompts** — use generic schema instructions instead.
2. **`console.error(error, requestBody)`** where `requestBody` contains intake answers.
3. **Storing transcript snippets or symptom text in `audit_log.payload`** for "debuggability".
4. **Sending PHI to AssemblyAI/Textract** when `processing_jobs.baa_verified` is false.
